jffgui - Class in jff.main
The class that starts the application GUI.
jffgui() - Constructor for class jff.main.jffgui
 
JFFMainFrame - Interface in jff.gui
The main Frame of the application.
JFFMainFrameImpl - Class in jff.gui
An implementation of JFFMainFrame.
The frame is divided in three parts, from up to down:
the files table (a JFFTable) the options tabbed panel (a JFFTabbedPane) the task table (a JFFTreeTable) It also provides a menu bar (a JFFMenuBar) and a tool bar (a JFFToolBar)
JFFMainFrameImpl() - Constructor for class jff.gui.JFFMainFrameImpl
Creates the items and the gui starting with the file in JFFPath.INITFILE
if the file isnt found then the item will be created with default parameters
JFFMainFrameImpl.JFFBundledItems - Class in jff.gui
A convenient group of the application items used to exchange all the data between actions and tables.
JFFMainFrameImpl.JFFBundledItems(String) - Constructor for class jff.gui.JFFMainFrameImpl.JFFBundledItems
Constructs the items with the directives found in the specified init file
JFFMainFrameImpl.JFFBundledItems() - Constructor for class jff.gui.JFFMainFrameImpl.JFFBundledItems
Constructs the items with the default parameters
JFFMainFrameImpl.RestartableThread - Class in jff.gui
A thread which can be restarted always and at any time
JFFMainFrameImpl.RestartableThread(Runnable) - Constructor for class jff.gui.JFFMainFrameImpl.RestartableThread
Create the RestartableThread (without starting it)
JFFMenuBar - Interface in jff.gui
The menu bar of the application
JFFMenuBarImpl - Class in jff.gui
The implementation of the menu bar of the application.
It consists of 5 menus with these menu items:
File AddFile DeleteFile ShowFiles HideFiles PlayFile Quit Select SelectAll SelectNone InvertSelection Options ShowOptions HideOptions Tasks AddTask DeleteTask PlayTasks PauseTasks ClearTasks Info Help Credits
JFFMenuBarImpl(Component, JFFTable, JFFTabbedPane, JFFTreeTable, JFFMainFrameImpl.JFFBundledItems) - Constructor for class jff.gui.JFFMenuBarImpl
Create the menu bar connecting the menu voices to their respective actions

JFFStrings - Interface in jff.translation
A collection of all the Strings displayed in the application.
Implemented to give a flexible translation system
JFFStringsImpl - Class in jff.translation
An implementation of JFFStrings.
When created, an instance of JFFStringsImpl will check in the INITFILE the language specified, then it will search in the LANGFOLDER a file with this name (with .txt as extension) and load the language written in it, using a JFFParser
JFFStringsImpl() - Constructor for class jff.translation.JFFStringsImpl
It will load the default language, "english" defined in JFFStringsImpl.Lang
JFFStringsImpl(BufferedReader) - Constructor for class jff.translation.JFFStringsImpl
It will load the language with the name defined in the INITFILE in the line
language: name
from the file LANGFOLDER/name.txt

JFFTabbedPaneImpl - Class in jff.gui.tabbedpane
